Step 1: Compute the Debt to Asset Ratio.
• From the balance sheet, Total Liabilities are given as “Total Current Liabilities” which equals 2,110,671.05.
• Total Assets are given as 16,213,861.65.
• Therefore, Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets = 2,110,671.05 / 16,213,861.65 ≈ 0.13.

Step 2: Compute the Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio.
• From the cash flow statement, the Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities is 1,598,438.00.
• From the income statement, the Net Profit is 1,103,190.60.
• Thus, Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio = 1,598,438.00 / 1,103,190.60 ≈ 1.45.

The final answer is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.13",
    "Operating Cash Flow to Net Income Ratio": "1.45"
  }
}
